    "headline": "Alcohol Sales Have Been Soft.  Constellation’s Earnings Will Tell Us More About Demand.",
    "summary": "Constellation’s  earnings report, set to release on Wednesday after the market closes, could give investors a better idea whether demand is picking up.  For the fourth quarter of fiscal 2026 that ended in February, analysts polled by FactSet expect sales at Constellation, the U.S. distributor of Corona and Modelo beers, to decline 13% from a year ago to $1.88 billion, while earnings are estimated at $1.71 per share compared with $2.63 during the same period last year.  In the first three quarters of fiscal 2026, Constellation’s beer sales decreased 4% year over year.",
